{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
'''Christian Social Responsibility''' (CSR, '''Kristet Samhällsansvar''') was a [[lobbying|lobby]] organization that was founded in the mid-1950s in Sweden. The goal of the organisation was to get [[Christian]] politicians placed high up on the voting papers of the Swedish political parties. The CSR had a grassroots network of active members over the entire nation and produced their own material. 

The chairman of the organisation was [[Centre Party (Sweden)|Centre Party]] voter Sven Danell. [[Lewi Pethrus]], one of the founders of the [[Christian Democrats (Sweden)|Christian Democratic Party]] was the vice chairman. [[Birger Ekstedt]], later to become the chairman of the Christian Democratic Party, was the secretary of the organisation.

