{{Infobox politician | name = Dan Diaconescu | image = Dan Diaconescu la BEC depune candidatura la presedintie 22.09.2014.png | imagesize = 170px | office1 = President of [[People's Party - Dan Diaconescu]] | term_start1 = | term_end1 = | predecessor1 = none (position established) | successor1 = [[Marin Diaconescu]] | party = [[People's Party – Dan Diaconescu]] | profession = journalist | nationality = Romanian | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1967|12|9|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Caracal, Romania|Caracal]], [[Socialist Republic of Romania|Romania]] | religion = [[Romanian Orthodox Church|Romanian Orthodox]] | alma_mater = [[Politehnica University of Bucharest]] }}
'''Dan Cristian Diaconescu''' ({{IPA-ro|dan di.akoˈnesku}}; born December 9, 1967, [[Caracal, Romania|Caracal]]) is a [[Romania]]n journalist, politician, presenter,<ref name="Heintz2006">{{cite book|last=Heintz|first=Monica|title="Be European, Recycle Yourself!": The Changing Work Ethic in Romania|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RfBYr8nRZgAC&pg=PA75|accessdate=16 July 2012|year=2006|publisher=LIT Verlag Münster|isbn=9783825899059|pages=75–}}</ref> the founder and present owner of [[DDTV]] and [[OTV (Romanian TV station)|OTV]] television stations. He graduated from the Faculty of Mechanical Engineering, part of the Polytechnic Institute of Bucharest. In 2010, together with OTV show presenters, he formed the [[People's Party – Dan Diaconescu]].
==Biography== Diaconescu graduated the Faculty of Mechanical Engineering of the [[Politehnica University of Bucharest|Polytechnic Institute of Bucharest]]. Diaconescu became famous because the show on OTV ''Dan Diaconescu Direct'' and Elodia series which took place in 2008-2009, during which the lawyer of the same name missing after an alleged crime, was wanted by the authorities and reporters OTV.
===Trial=== On 22 June 2010, Diaconescu was arrested by the National Anti-corruption Agency (DNA) for extortion. Diaconescu was accused of having asked a mayor of a commune in Transylvania to take money in exchange for not publishing compromising data. A day later, he was arrested for 29 days, following the District 1 Court's decision. On 25 June, Diaconescu was released after Bucharest Court judges have upheld the decision of detention.
"I want to tell you that from this moment Dona, my daughter holds OTV and I announce my candidacy for the next presidential elections in 2014 or when are they" were the first words spoken by Dan Diaconescu, after he left the arrest.
==Political activity== On 29 November 2010, Diaconescu founded the People's Party, the party idea based on a citizen residing in Cugir. He launched his candidacy for the [[Romanian presidential election, 2014|presidential election in 2014]].
At the [[Romanian legislative election, 2012|legislative election of 2012]], Diaconescu was nominated to run for a deputy term of Gorj in one electoral college against his challenger was then prime minister, [[Victor Ponta]]. He lost the election, and missed the entrance to the Parliament on redistribution. Therefore, he announced his retirement from politics.
==Controversies== OTV was two times subject to license withdrawal by the Romanian Authority in Audiovisual CNA, first in 2002 for racism and antisemitic attitude,<ref>{{cite web|title=Ev.Z. (2002) |url=http://www.evz.ro/detalii/stiri/otv-mereu-peste-lege-522445.html |publisher=Evenimentul Zilei }}{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and second in January 2013 after OTV failed to prove payment of fines imposed by CNA for breaches of the Audiovisual Law during years 2009, 2010, 2011, and 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mediafax (ian. 2013)|url=http://www.mediafax.ro/cultura-media/cna-a-retras-licenta-audiovizuala-a-otv-postul-si-a-incetat-emisia-marti-seara-10516268|publisher=Mediafax}}</ref>
