'''Luhanga''' is a village in [[North Kivu]], the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].<ref name="africanews34civilianskilledinhutu">{{cite news|title=DRC: 34 civilians killed in Hutu village|url=http://www.africanews.com/2016/11/27/drc-34-civilians-killed-in-hutu-village-by-nande-militiamen//|accessdate=February 20, 2017|work=Africanews|date=November 27, 2016}}</ref> It is populated by [[Hutu]]s.<ref name="africanews34civilianskilledinhutu"/> On November 27, 2016, [[Nande language|Nande]]s came into the village and killed 34 Hutus.<ref name="africanews34civilianskilledinhutu"/>

