==Notes==
*Three former top 16 players re-enter that group. They are [[Joe Perry (snooker player)|Joe Perry]], [[Marco Fu]] and [[Mark King (snooker player)|Mark King]]. *[[Mark Allen (snooker player)|Mark Allen]] is the only new member of the top 16. *The players to drop out the top 16 are long standing top 16 players: [[Stephen Lee (snooker player)|Stephen Lee]] (a member of the top 16 for 11 consecutive seasons), [[Mark Williams (snooker player)|Mark Williams]] (for 12), [[Ken Doherty]] (for 15) and [[Steve Davis]]. *Players to reach career high rankings within the top 16 are: [[Stephen Maguire]] No.2, [[Mark Selby]] No.4, [[Allister Carter]] No.7, [[Ryan Day]] No.8, Joe Perry No.12, Marco Fu No.14 and Mark Allen No.16. *No new players reach the top 32, however two players return: former world No.9 [[Fergal O'Brien]] at No.24 and [[Michael Judge]] at No.30. Two players drop out: [[Gerard Greene]] and [[Michael Holt (snooker player)|Michael Holt]] to 33rd and 34th place respectively. *Other players to reach career high rankings within the top 64 are: [[Jamie Cope]] up to No.19, [[Stuart Bingham]] No.21, [[Ricky Walden]] No.35, [[Andrew Higginson]] No.38, [[Liang Wenbo]] No.40, [[Judd Trump]] No.41, [[David Gilbert (snooker player)|David Gilbert]] No.43, [[Rory McLeod (snooker player)|Rory McLeod]] No.44, [[Jimmy Michie]] No.46, [[Mike Dunn (snooker player)|Mike Dunn]] No.47, [[Tom Ford (snooker player)|Tom Ford]] No.48, [[Liu Song (snooker player)|Liu Song]] No.53 and [[Ian Preece]] No.55. New players to enter the top 64 are [[Mark Joyce]] at No.59, [[Martin Gould]] No.63 and [[David Morris (snooker player)|David Morris]] No.64. *Former top player [[Jimmy White]] fall out the top 64 to 65th place, but remained on the tour via the one year list. *Former top 32 player [[Robin Hull]] retired from the main tour due to illness.
